Assessments were meant to kick off today at several locations off-campus. CAPE TOWN The Cape Peninsula University of Technology has postponed this week s exams.Assessments were meant to kick off today at several locations off-campus.But there have been threats by anti-fees protesters to disrupt exams.The institution s Lauren Kansley says, During a late-night meeting between university stakeholders, which includes the Fees Must Fall activists, the SRC and our union representatives, the decision to postpone our exams by one week was taken. This is since the majority of CPUT students were supposed to write their exams today. CPUT management yesterday obtained an urgent interim court interdict as a precaution.(Edited by Leeto M Khoza)